1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:11,537
=The Moment I Met You=

2
00:00:11,537 --> 00:00:15,000
=Episode 1=

3
00:00:22,775 --> 00:00:25,312
(Mao Buyu, Civet Lord)

4
00:00:26,839 --> 00:00:28,280
Mao Buyu, the Civet Lord.

5
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:32,119
You've hidden among
the Embroidered Guard for years.

6
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,679
You've served His Majesty.

7
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,759
The land is plagued
by bandits as of late.

8
00:00:37,039 --> 00:00:38,320
As a commander,

9
00:00:39,119 --> 00:00:40,439
you are equally responsible.

10
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:44,880
You are ordered to go undercover at
the Ministry of Justice as a constable.

11
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:48,320
You are to capture the notorious
outlaw leader, the Jade Squirrel.

12
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,640
The thief's movements are unpredictable.

13
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:52,640
He is a major threat
to the Imperial Court.

14
00:00:53,159 --> 00:00:54,399
The stakes are incredibly high.

15
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:56,960
Do not compromise your identity
as an Embroidered Guard.

16
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:57,840
I shall

17
00:00:58,960 --> 00:00:59,600
obey the order.

18
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,862
(Mao's Residence)

19
00:01:05,159 --> 00:01:05,799
Buyu!

20
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:06,760
Buyu...

21
00:01:07,159 --> 00:01:07,760
Dad!

22
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,040
You little rascal!

23
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:11,319
You actually became an undercover
for the Gate Bureau!

24
00:01:12,519 --> 00:01:13,079
(Mao Wenrong, Chief Constable, Intel Corps)
Buyu!

25
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,000
Buyu!

26
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:15,840
Director Liu.

27
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:16,560
(Director of Personnel, Liu Sanhuai)
Buyu.

28
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,359
Commissioner Luo signed the decree.

29
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,280
Starting today,

30
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,480
you are officially
a Gate Bureau's constable.

31
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:23,920
Buyu, I knew it.

32
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:26,760
I knew you wouldn't settle
for being a street loafer forever.

33
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:28,280
You're turning your life around.

34
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:30,200
The Mao legacy is in your hands now.

35
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:32,719
Look, Buyu.

36
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,920
Your constable uniform is right here.

37
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,760
Dad, Director Liu,

38
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,760
I just remembered
something very important.

39
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,640
I have to take care of it right now.

40
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,200
Dad, no...

41
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,040
Don't worry!

42
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,120
- I'll be back!
- Buyu!

43
00:01:44,130 --> 00:01:45,852
- Where are you going?
- Buyu! Where you're going?

44
00:01:45,984 --> 00:01:47,870
(Yunchang's Flower Shop)

45
00:01:50,512 --> 00:01:53,462
(Chu Yunchang, The Jade Squirrel)

46
00:01:57,719 --> 00:01:58,120
Chang!

47
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:58,719
Oh no.

48
00:01:58,920 --> 00:01:59,760
I'm hurt.

49
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,400
Let me see it.

50
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,840
How bad is it?

51
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,719
Zhizhi!

52
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,560
Quick, get the medicine
before Buyu's scratch heals itself.

53
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,520
What brings you by?

54
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,800
I'm here to tell you some great news.

55
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:15,280
I'm officially a constable
for the Gate Bureau.

56
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,000
What?

57
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,680
From now on, no one will ever
mess with you again.

58
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,360
Chang,

59
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,080
I want you to meet my father.

60
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:28,599
Meet your father?

61
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:32,280
I want my father
to propose to your family.

62
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,560
(Zhizhi, the Poison Master)
I didn't know you were here, Mao.

63
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:42,199
It's nothing.

64
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,840
I should get going.

65
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:45,840
Be careful.

66
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,240
What is wrong with this world?

67
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,560
I can't believe Buyu
joined the Gate Bureau.

68
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:52,719
Sister,

69
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,360
I think you're actually pretty lucky.

70
00:02:55,439 --> 00:02:56,439
You start off

71
00:02:56,439 --> 00:02:58,560
by crossing paths
with such a dangerous man.

72
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,719
What are you going to do?

73
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,199
Are you still

74
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,240
going to meet his parents
this afternoon?

75
00:03:04,039 --> 00:03:05,190
Maybe you should just skip it.

76
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,680
I must go.

77
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:08,080
Of course I'm going.

78
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,280
So what if he's a constable?

79
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,280
Nothing to be afraid of.

80
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,919
It's not like

81
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:13,800
his entire family is constables.

82
00:03:14,837 --> 00:03:15,737
(Master Constables)

83
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,250
(No Thieves Under Heaven)

84
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:19,360
(I'm toast.)

85
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,719
(Buyu's entire family are
master constables.)

86
00:03:22,719 --> 00:03:25,080
(I'm a mouse in a cat's den.)

87
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,000
Chang,

88
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,159
(Mao Jixian, Chief of the Probe Corps)
this is my father.

89
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,960
He's the Chief of the Probe Corps
at the Gate Bureau.

90
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,840
Greetings, Chief Mao.

91
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,639
This is my older sister,

92
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,120
Mao Wenrong from
the Gate Bureau's Intel Corps.

93
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,439
Hi, Sister Rong.

94
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,960
And this is my brother-in-law,

95
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:42,400
(Xu Anran, Chief Coroner)
Xu Anran, the Chief Coroner.

96
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,439
Ms. Chu.

97
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,080
Mind your own business.

98
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,520
Ms. Chu,

99
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:49,120
what exactly do you do for a living?

100
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,479
I run a flower shop.

101
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,240
It's a small business,

102
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,400
but it's enough to support me

103
00:03:54,599 --> 00:03:55,199
and Buyu.

104
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:56,840
Ms. Chu,

105
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:59,520
the Mao family is
a lineage of constables.

106
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:03,120
Every member, man or woman,
serves the Gate Bureau.

107
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,000
Our teachings are clear.

108
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:07,000
If a Mao is to marry,

109
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,599
their spouse must also be
from the Gate Bureau.

110
00:04:10,159 --> 00:04:10,800
Is that clear?

111
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,360
Dad, don't be so rigid.

112
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:16,480
Buyu,

113
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,720
as a member of the Gate Bureau,

114
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,720
I expect you to marry

115
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,480
a woman connected to the Bureau.

116
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,240
She can support you,

117
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,040
understand you, and assist you.

118
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:27,120
It will let you focus on solving cases

119
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,920
without any worries at home.

120
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,279
And what about love?

121
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,399
Love is something you grow into.

122
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,720
Look at my sister.

123
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,800
You forced her to marry  Anran.

124
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,680
I haven't seen

125
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,920
much love between them.

126
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:38,839
- Why you!
- You!

127
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,720
Darling,

128
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,480
have some fruit.

129
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,560
What makes you think

130
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,920
my husband and I aren't happy?

131
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:46,720
Honey, have some fruit.

132
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,360
Eat up!

133
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,120
Yes.

134
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:50,920
Sister,

135
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,040
give it a rest.

136
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,120
Your acting is terrible.

137
00:04:53,279 --> 00:04:55,120
In any case, I will never approve

138
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,720
of you marrying a woman who isn't

139
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,360
with the Gate Bureau.

140
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,240
Over my dead body!

141
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:01,399
Dad, please.

142
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,480
Stop with the dark talk.

143
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,560
Chang, you wanted to see me?

144
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:18,720
Your family doesn't like me.

145
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,900
I don't want to hold you back.

146
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,360
We should break up.

147
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,560
Is that all the faith

148
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,600
you have in our love?

149
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,639
Even if we aren't together,

150
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,720
we can still be friends.

151
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:33,560
How can I just be friends with
the girl I fell for at first sight?

152
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,279
You need to cool off.

153
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:42,839
Chang,

154
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,040
I've fallen for you

155
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,279
since I first saw you.

156
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,839
I'm not letting you go.

157
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,560
And don't ever say that again.

158
00:05:49,959 --> 00:05:51,079
You won't regret it?

159
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:53,720
No matter what happens,

160
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:55,199
you won't give up on me?

161
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:56,160
Never.

162
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,759
I already told my father.

163
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:00,790
As soon as I crack a major case,

164
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,639
I'm marrying you.

165
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:04,839
It's not that simple.

166
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,399
It used to be tough.

167
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:07,959
But now,

168
00:06:08,399 --> 00:06:09,160
all I just need to

169
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,639
catch the notorious

170
00:06:10,639 --> 00:06:11,279
Jade Squirrel.

171
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:15,959
The Jade Squirrel?

172
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,839
Let me tell you,

173
00:06:17,839 --> 00:06:18,959
that squirrel is our ticket

174
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,079
to a life together.

175
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,600
I have to get to work.

176
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:24,399
I'll come find you in a few days.

177
00:06:29,519 --> 00:06:30,279
(Fool.)

178
00:06:30,959 --> 00:06:33,720
(The rodent you're hunting is me.)

179
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:41,275
(The Queen of Thieves, Chu Xiangling)

180
00:06:41,519 --> 00:06:42,839
(The King of Thieves, Mei Guangzu)
The Nine-Dragon Lovers' Censer.

181
00:06:43,079 --> 00:06:45,600
This is an heirloom from
the wealthiest family in the capital.

182
00:06:45,839 --> 00:06:47,160
It's worth a massive fortune.

183
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:50,279
Now check this out.

184
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,600
The Dust-Repelling Pearl.

185
00:06:51,959 --> 00:06:52,959
If you keep this on you,

186
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:53,959
you stay spotless

187
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:55,639
even after traveling a thousand li.

188
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:56,759
This is a real treasure.

189
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,319
Nice work, darling.

190
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:04,439
Auntie, Uncle.

191
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,519
Didn't we have a deal?

192
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:06,639
No more stealing.

193
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:07,720
I...

194
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:09,199
We weren't stealing.

195
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:11,399
We were just teaching a little lesson

196
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:13,279
to some petty thieves on our turf.

197
00:07:13,439 --> 00:07:13,839
Exactly.

198
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:14,639
Save the excuses.

199
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:15,759
Stealing is stealing.

200
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:16,839
Well...

201
00:07:16,959 --> 00:07:18,600
Fine, fine. It won't happen again.

202
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:19,959
Just this once, right?

203
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,600
Chang,

204
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:22,759
I heard

205
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:24,879
you met Mao Buyu's parents today.

206
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:26,959
What does

207
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,639
the Mao family do for a living?

208
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:30,519
I sent you two out on a job.

209
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,839
Why are you back so late?

210
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,439
What exactly does this Mao Buyu do?

211
00:07:34,439 --> 00:07:35,120
Come on, tell us.

212
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,680
Tell us!

213
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:43,759
What's the big secret?

214
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,279
Dad,

215
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:46,720
Buyu is way too naive.

216
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:48,759
He hasn't even checked her background,

217
00:07:48,959 --> 00:07:50,439
yet he's planning a life with her.

218
00:07:50,839 --> 00:07:51,879
You can't let this stand.

219
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,319
Rong,

220
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,720
aren't we being a bit too harsh

221
00:07:56,079 --> 00:07:57,720
on Chu Yunchang?

222
00:07:58,199 --> 00:07:59,199
What are you saying?

223
00:08:00,639 --> 00:08:02,839
We've only met her once.

224
00:08:02,839 --> 00:08:03,959
We don't really know her,

225
00:08:04,199 --> 00:08:05,439
yet we rejected her outright.

226
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:07,279
It's no wonder Buyu is pushing back.

227
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:09,279
If she's not with the Gate Bureau,

228
00:08:09,519 --> 00:08:10,959
she has no place in this family.

229
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,319
That may be true,

230
00:08:14,639 --> 00:08:16,480
but we need a solid reason

231
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,000
to actually convince Buyu.

232
00:08:18,712 --> 00:08:19,775
(Yunchang's Flower Shop)

233
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,759
Is this the place?

234
00:08:21,759 --> 00:08:22,759
Chief Mao!

235
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,639
Chief Mao!

236
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,519
What?

237
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:27,639
This is the flower shop
Buyu always visits.

238
00:08:32,399 --> 00:08:34,039
Watch out, those flowers have thorns.

239
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,600
It's fine.

240
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,759
See? I told you so.

241
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,360
Today is your birthday.

242
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:45,759
Tell me what you want,

243
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,279
and it's yours.

244
00:08:47,879 --> 00:08:49,480
Aren't you afraid of my thorns?

245
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:52,000
I wouldn't care
even if you were a cactus.

246
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,000
Dad? Sister?

247
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:01,039
What are you doing here?

248
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:02,879
We were just passing by.

249
00:09:03,759 --> 00:09:04,759
We thought we'd stop in.

250
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,399
Chief Mao. Rong.

251
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:07,639
Please, come in.

252
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,759
So, this is your shop?

253
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:11,639
Rong,

254
00:09:11,639 --> 00:09:13,240
if anything catches your eye,

255
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,279
it's on the house.

256
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:14,879
Nothing.

257
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:17,639
Yunchang,

258
00:09:18,039 --> 00:09:19,879
who else is in your family?

259
00:09:38,519 --> 00:09:39,879
Allow me to introduce everyone.

260
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:41,519
This is my aunt,

261
00:09:41,639 --> 00:09:42,759
and this is my uncle.

262
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:44,879
Nice to meet you.

263
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,159
Hello, everyone.

264
00:09:46,279 --> 00:09:47,759
Why didn't your aunt and uncle

265
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,279
use the front door?

266
00:09:50,639 --> 00:09:52,279
It's a family tradition

267
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,399
to take the unusual path.

268
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,759
Besides, it's great exercise.

269
00:09:54,759 --> 00:09:55,620
Two birds with one stone.

270
00:09:55,639 --> 00:09:56,519
Exactly.

271
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:57,860
It's good for your health.

272
00:09:57,879 --> 00:09:58,759
Yeah.

273
00:10:02,639 --> 00:10:04,399
This is Buyu's father,

274
00:10:04,399 --> 00:10:05,759
and this lady is his sister.

275
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,360
Chief Mao. Ms. Mao.

276
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:12,759
Chief Mao, what brings you here today?

277
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,039
Well, I...

278
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:18,159
Today is Chang's birthday,

279
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:21,480
so I brought my father
for a proper introduction.

280
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,039
I'm not marrying anyone but Chang.

281
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:27,399
My father was getting anxious,

282
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:28,879
so he wanted to meet you both.

283
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:32,039
I see. In that case,

284
00:10:32,639 --> 00:10:33,399
please come in.

285
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:37,519
Wait, we haven't prepared anything yet.

286
00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:38,639
Prepare what?

287
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:41,639
Is there something in this house
you're trying to hide?

288
00:10:41,639 --> 00:10:42,519
No!

289
00:10:42,799 --> 00:10:44,399
Most things here are best kept hidden.

290
00:10:47,519 --> 00:10:50,000
(A family of constables
meets a family of fugitives.)

291
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:51,519
(Yunchang,)

292
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:53,159
(this is your ultimate test.)

293
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,390
(We can't let this whole thing
go down in flames today.)

294
00:11:03,187 --> 00:11:06,462
♪Grudges and regrets
are like strong wine♪

295
00:11:06,512 --> 00:11:09,387
♪Drink it down and let it go♪

296
00:11:09,662 --> 00:11:15,380
♪An empty cup for our love and hate♪

297
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:20,180
♪Tears blur a fate I can't control♪

298
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:23,100
♪Let's drink until dawn♪

299
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:29,340
♪Behind this mask, I'll never lie♪

300
00:11:30,787 --> 00:11:33,180
♪Every reunion feels like the first♪

301
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:36,830
♪This hidden smile will never fade♪

302
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:40,390
♪One heart, standing by your side♪

303
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,575
♪To the ends of time♪

304
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:46,862
♪The moon traces your face♪

305
00:11:46,937 --> 00:11:50,662
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

306
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:57,060
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

307
00:11:57,125 --> 00:12:00,340
♪A silent prayer in my soul♪

308
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:04,175
♪Carrying my vow beneath the moon♪

309
00:12:04,487 --> 00:12:07,512
♪Hoping we never drift apart again♪

310
00:12:07,512 --> 00:12:10,612
♪On our way to forever♪

311
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:14,500
♪The moon traces your face♪

312
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,860
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

313
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:24,180
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

314
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:34,740
♪Just to be with you♪

